#Read Quality Control#
Oxford Nanopore Reads

1. NanoPlot \
--fastq Combined_reads_ont.fastq.gz \
--loglength \
-o NanoPlot

2. gunzip -c Combined_reads_ont.fastq.gz | \
NanoFilt -q 8 -l 1000 | \
gzip > ONT_filtered_q8_l1000.fastq.gz

3. Illumina Reads
fastqc \
R1.fastq.gz \
R2.fastq.gz

4. Genome Assembly
Filtered ONT reads were supplied as long-read input, whereas Hi-C paired-end reads were provided using the --h1 and --h2 parameters.
hifiasm \
--ont \
-t 80 \
--h1 LB0111_good_1.fq.gz \
--h2 LB0111_good_2.fq.gz \
-o LB0111_ont_hic.asm \
ONT_filtered_q8_l1000.fastq.gz


5. Assembly Quality Assessment
quast.py \
LB0111_ont_hic.p_ctg.fa \
--large \
-o quast
Genome completeness was evaluated using BUSCO v5.4.3 with the Aves lineage dataset.
Example command:
busco \
-i LB0111_ont_hic.p_ctg.fa \
-l aves_odb10 \
-o busco_aves \
-m genome \
-c 80


6. Hi-C Read Mapping
Representative commands:
bwa-mem2 index LB0111_ont_hic.p_ctg.fa
bwa-mem2 mem \
-t 80 \
LB0111_ont_hic.p_ctg.fa \
LB0111_good_1.fq.gz \
LB0111_good_2.fq.gz | \
samtools sort \
-o hic.sorted.bam

samtools index hic.sorted.bam

7. Hi-C Scaffolding Evaluation
yahs \
LB0111_ont_hic.p_ctg.fa \
hic.sorted.bam

